In [176]:
#deleting outliers that were seen in Box Plot
for cols in df.columns:
    if df[cols].dtype == 'int64' or df[cols].dtype == 'float64':
        upper_range = df[cols].mean() + 3 * df[cols].std()
        lower_range = df[cols].mean() - 3 * df[cols].std()
        
        indexs = df[(df[cols] > upper_range) | (df[cols] < lower_range)].index
        df = df.drop(indexs)

#RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn import metrics

def RandomForest(xtrain, ytrain, xtest, ytest):
    randomForest = RandomForestRegressor()
    randomForest.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
    y_pred = randomForest.predict(xtest)
    
    #accurracy messaures    
    print('MAE:', metrics.mean_absolute_error(ytest, y_pred))
    print('MSE:', metrics.mean_squared_error(ytest, y_pred))
    print('R2_score:', metrics.r2_score(ytest, y_pred))

RandomForest(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test)

MSE: 0.2730138942881502
R2_score: 0.9879941675051541

#gradient boosting
from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor

#maxdepth: 20, minsamleaf: 117, n: 73, maxfeat: 10, lr: 0.07
def gradientboostingmachine(md, msl, n, mf, lr, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    gbm_best = GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=n, random_state=1111,
                                         max_depth=md, max_features=mf, 
                                         min_samples_leaf=msl, learning_rate=lr
                                         )
    gbm_best.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred_gbm = gbm_best.predict(X_test)
   
    print('MAE:', metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred_gbm))
    print('MSE:', metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_gbm))
    print('R2_score:', metrics.r2_score(y_test, y_pred_gbm))

gradientboostingmachine(20, 117, 73, 10, 0.07, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test) 

MAE: 1.156736184491294
MSE: 3.5558096245471598
R2_score: 0.8436326662158194

It is a regression problem and I used Random Forest Regressor and Gradient Boosting Regressor for prediction.Random Forest Regressor proved to be a better model between the two. Hypertuning the parameters further can increase the accuracy. A wide and deep model would also have been a great option, given there is a lot more time available
